- A 2x5 storyboard grid of 10 frames for a 15-second photorealistic CGI animated short film, BBC Planet Earth documentary aesthetic, macro cinematography, rich greens and golden hour light, natural soft shadows, extreme scale shifts from micro to macro.

Theme: a single seed's journey blown by wind, surviving a storm, slowly growing into a great tree full of life.

Frames: (1) extreme wide autumn forest, single seed released from a tall tree, golden bokeh background;

(2) macro tracking shot - seed floating through air, passing insects and leaves, delicate and small;

(3) slow-motion impact - seed lands on soft soil, dirt particles scatter, raindrop falls beside it;

(4) surreal underground macro - roots beginning to grow in darkness, microscopic and beautiful;

(5) wide dramatic shot - violent storm raging, everything uprooted, but the seed's spot stays still;

(6) macro close-up - first green sprout breaking through soil, morning dew on tip, sunlight catching it;

(7) accelerated growth sequence - sapling rising, seasons shifting, light and shadow changing, alive;

(8) wide shot - juvenile tree now standing, birds arriving, leaves rustling gently in wind;

(9) medium warm shot - children playing in the tree's shade, a bird building a nest in the branches;

(10) mirror wide shot - framed from the angle of the original tall tree, the new great tree now stands in its place circle of life.

